{"id": "duc04-testb-15:9#28", "contents": "The funeral service was a powerful tribute to Shepard's life and legacy, with many speakers reflecting on the lessons he taught through his courage and compassion. The Rev. Royce Brown, pastor of St. Mark's, drew a poignant comparison between Shepard's death and the crucifixion of Jesus Christ, saying, \"I replace that image with that of another man hung upon a cross. When I concentrate on that man, I can release the bitterness inside.\" As the service came to a close, Shepard's family was visibly moved by the outpouring of support, with his father, Dennis, expressing his gratitude for the \"thousands of e-mail comments, Web-site messages, phone calls and cards offering help, consolation, sympathy and support.\""}
